        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 5:15PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 515 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Pleasant Gap to near Talladega Superspeedway.
Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Graham, Morrison Cross Roads, Newell, Barfield, Coleman Lake And
Campground, Woodland, Edwardsville, Trickem, Lake Cleburne, Heflin,
Liberty Hill, Micaville, Oak Level, Corinth, Gunthertown, Hollis
Crossroads, Muscadine, Abernathy, Fosters Cross Roads, and Sweetwater
Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
